note[incorrect-using-for]: `using ... for` names a library with no function applicable to the type, so the directive attaches nothing
   ╭▸ ROOT/testdata/IncorrectUsingFor.sol:LL:CC
   │
LL │ using StringLib for Point;
   │       ━━━━━━━━━
   │
   ╰ help: https://getfoundry.sh/forge/linting/incorrect-using-for

note[incorrect-using-for]: `using ... for` names a library with no function applicable to the type, so the directive attaches nothing
   ╭▸ ROOT/testdata/IncorrectUsingFor.sol:LL:CC
   │
LL │     using StringLib for uint256;
   │           ━━━━━━━━━
   │
   ╰ help: https://getfoundry.sh/forge/linting/incorrect-using-for

note[incorrect-using-for]: `using ... for` names a library with no function applicable to the type, so the directive attaches nothing
   ╭▸ ROOT/testdata/IncorrectUsingFor.sol:LL:CC
   │
LL │     using PrivateLib for Holder;
   │           ━━━━━━━━━━
   │
   ╰ help: https://getfoundry.sh/forge/linting/incorrect-using-for

